race.comment: PRINCE OF BROOKY (2) has been about the mark in three runs this time in, perhaps not seeing out the 1462m last time at Kilmore. His two runs prior were good and he should take plenty of catching. UNA GENTLE (13) ran a solid race fresh over 1000m at Bairnsdale, just fading late there to finish fourth. She'll be fitter and 1200m suits better. HEALING FREQUENCY (9) filly by Impending out of Secret Selection who makes debut. Has had four hit-outs leading into this, the latest when fourth in a Flemington jump-out. Watch for any market confidence. LOTTA CITY (10) filly by Ilovethiscity out of Charlotta on debut. Showing promise leading into this, placing in a couple of recent jump-outs. Well placed to make an immediate impact.
